Also, the eligibility for promotion of the officers concerned will not be checked in the rolls for the next two years. Thereafter, if the officer concerned qualifies for promotion on merits, his / her name will be considered for inclusion in the regular selection list.

Officers being promoted under this order shall give the option of fixation of pay within one month from the date of assumption of office. If such an option is not given, their salary should be fixed taking into account the prevailing rules.

If the officers being promoted under this order do not appear at the place of appointment on promotion or attempt to make the appointment elsewhere under royal pressure, the confidential report of the officers concerned shall be recorded accordingly. It is also to be noted that disciplinary action will be taken against the officer concerned as the act of Royal Pressure violates Rule 3 (3) and 23 of the Maharashtra Civil Services (Conduct) Rules, 1979.
